title: Correction in 'Developer Tutorial' page
body: I was going through the tutorial and I found a place where the documentation was not precise. Under **Adding JavaScript transaction logic** the `logic.js` files are present in two different directories. First in `lib` and other in `test`. I would seriously encourage you to mention it explicitly to make changes to `logic.js` under `lib` repo.

title: A small correction to 'Deploying to a single organization Hyperledger Fabric' Page
body:
In Step Eight, the command mentioned is `composer network start -c PeerAdmin@fabric-network -a tutorial-network.bna -A admin -S adminpw` but the `.bna` file created in the Developer Tutorial is `tutorial-network@0.0.1.bna` So I propose that the modified command on the page 'Deploying to a single organization Hyperledger Fabric' be `composer network start -c PeerAdmin@fabric-network -a tutorial-network\@0.0.1.bna -A admin -S adminpw`

I leave the rest to the developers to decide. Just a small suggestion from my end
